Iavan Pijoos, News24Police. (News24, file) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Thohoyandou - A mob of residents in Thohoyandou murdered a man and set his body alight at the weekend, &nbsp;Limpopo police said on Sunday.&nbsp; Lieutenant Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe said the body of a 25-year-old man was found beside a street in the town by passers-by on Sunday morning.&nbsp; "It is alleged that the deceased was attacked by a group of people who killed him and then burnt him to ashes," Ngoepe said.&nbsp; The motive behind the killing was still unknown and the man has not yet been identified.&nbsp;No arrests had been made.&nbsp; Provincial commissioner Lieutenant General Nneke Ledwaba has called on residents to refrain from taking the law into their own hands.&nbsp; 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.